<title>USA: Binks Sames Q1 net hurt by plant closing.</title>
<headline>Binks Sames Q1 net hurt by plant closing.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKLIN PARK, Ill. 1997-04-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Binks Sames Corp said Friday its earnings fell in the first quarter ended February 28 from a year ago, due to diminished production at its Franklin Park plant ahead of the shut down of the plant.</p>
<p>Production ended at Franklin Park on February 20.</p>
<p>&quot;We anticipated that our operating results would be weak during early fiscal 1997 because of the restructuring initiatives undertaken by the company late last year,&quot; Binks Sames chairman John Schornack said.</p>
<p>Earlier Friday, Binks Sames said net income fell to $142,000, or $0.05 a share a year ago, compared to $1.1 million, or $0.36 a share a year ago.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
